<title>UK: Micro Focus down as ceo cashes in options.</title>
<headline>Micro Focus down as ceo cashes in options.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-06-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Micro Focus Group Plc dropped on Wednesday as the software group said its chief executive Marcelo Gumucio cashed in share options.</p>
<p>The stock was down 45p or 2.4 percent at 18.70 stg by 1243 GMT, in thin trade of 3,500 shares.</p>
<p>Micro Focus said Gumucio had exercised options to acquire 72,500 shares at 653p and 2,000 shares at 6.05p, and had sold 74,500 shares at 18.45 stg.</p>
<p>The stock reached a near-four year high of 18.82-1/2 stg on June 16.</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 4367</p>
